  • Deprecated Methods 
    Method and Description
    oracle.kv.table.TableAPI.execute(String)
    since 3.3 in favor of KVStore.execute(java.util.List<oracle.kv.Operation>)
    oracle.kv.table.TableAPI.executeSync(String)
    since 3.3 in favor of KVStore.executeSync(java.lang.String)
    oracle.kv.KVStore.getAvroCatalog()
    as of 4.0, use the table API instead.
    oracle.kv.stats.NodeMetrics.getDataCenterName()
    replaced by NodeMetrics.getZoneName()
    oracle.kv.table.RecordDef.getField(int)
    as of 4.2 Use getFieldDef(int)
    oracle.kv.table.RecordDef.getField(String)
    as of 4.2 Use getFieldDef(String)
    oracle.kv.table.RecordValue.getFields()
    as of 4.2 Please use the equivalent getFieldNames() method.
    oracle.kv.table.RecordDef.getFields()
    as of 4.2 Use getFieldNames()
    oracle.kv.table.StringDef.getMax()
    as of release 4.0 it is no longer possible to specify ranges on String types.
    oracle.kv.table.LongDef.getMax()
    as of release 4.0 it is no longer possible to specify ranges on Long types.
    oracle.kv.table.IntegerDef.getMax()
    as of release 4.0 it is no longer possible to specify ranges on Integer types. A storage size argument can be specified on an Integer type when used in a primary key.
    oracle.kv.table.FloatDef.getMax()
    as of release 4.0 it is no longer possible to specify ranges on Float types. A storage size argument can be specified on a Float type when used in a primary key.
    oracle.kv.table.DoubleDef.getMax()
    as of release 4.0 it is no longer possible to specify ranges on Double types.
    oracle.kv.StoreIteratorConfig.getMaxResultsBatches()
    since 3.4, no longer supported. Returns the value set by setMaxResultsBatches().
    oracle.kv.table.TableIteratorOptions.getMaxResultsBatches()
    since 3.4, no longer supported. Returns the value set by deprecated TableIteratorOptions constructor.
    oracle.kv.table.StringDef.getMin()
    as of release 4.0 it is no longer possible to specify ranges on String types.
    oracle.kv.table.LongDef.getMin()
    as of release 4.0 it is no longer possible to specify ranges on Long types.
    oracle.kv.table.IntegerDef.getMin()
    as of release 4.0 it is no longer possible to specify ranges on Integer types. A storage size argument can be specified on an Integer type when used in a primary key.
    oracle.kv.table.FloatDef.getMin()
    as of release 4.0 it is no longer possible to specify ranges on Float types. A storage size argument can be specified on a Float type when used in a primary key.
    oracle.kv.table.DoubleDef.getMin()
    as of release 4.0 it is no longer possible to specify ranges on Double types.
    oracle.kv.KVStoreConfig.getOpenTimeout(TimeUnit)
    replaced by KVStoreConfig.getSocketOpenTimeout(java.util.concurrent.TimeUnit)
    oracle.kv.stats.KVStats.getStoreIteratorMetrics()
    since 3.4, no longer supported. All of the methods of the returned StoreIteratorMetrics object will return 0.
    oracle.kv.table.StringDef.isMaxInclusive()
    as of release 4.0 it is no longer possible to specify ranges on String types.
    oracle.kv.table.StringDef.isMinInclusive()
    as of release 4.0 it is no longer possible to specify ranges on String types.
    oracle.kv.lob.PartialLOBException.isPartiallyDeleted()
    Use the getPartialStateMethod() instead
    oracle.kv.StoreIteratorConfig.setMaxResultsBatches(int)
    since 3.4, no longer supported.
    oracle.kv.KVStoreConfig.setOpenTimeout(long, TimeUnit)
    replaced by KVStoreConfig.setSocketOpenTimeout(long, java.util.concurrent.TimeUnit)
